snippet.textDisplay: "Maori haka haka, unleash the tiger" Dude, I'm Maori and that was a cool fucking mention. If no one is aware, the haka (one of them) is a traditional war dance Maori would perform before battle to intimidate and proclaim strength over an enemy. So in a way, the haka in the context of the song is about preparing yourself for battle as evident in "unleash the tiger." Ready, ready then unleash.
